cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.DC 

This paper is about a system for dynamic analysis of malware applications on Android devices. The primary focus is on security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE) as the authors propose a new system for analyzing malware behavior. The system involves monitoring and controlling the environment in which the application is executed, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The authors also mention the use of machine learning techniques to extract features from the application, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Lastly, the authors evaluate the performance of their system in terms of code coverage, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
